{"timestamp": "2025-12-06 17:31:55.309084", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nSummary assessment\\n- Overall infrastructure control-plane (OSPF) and server-farm connectivity appear healthy.\\n- Critical service outage detected: central DHCP server is not running.\\n- End-user hosts on access segments are not obtaining IP addresses via DHCP, leaving them without Layer-3 connectivity (no IP and no routes), thus unable to reach DNS or web services.\\n\\nObserved anomalies and impact\\n1) User hosts lack IPv4 configuration\\n- host_1_1_1_1 and host_2_1_1_1 show no IPv4 addresses or routes:\\n  - ip addr: eth0 has no inet address; ip route is empty on both hosts.\\n  - /etc/resolv.conf points to nameserver 10.200.0.2 (correct DNS), but hosts cannot use DNS because they have no IP connectivity.\\n  - Pings from these hosts to dns_server (10.200.0.2) and load_balancer (10.200.0.7) fail immediately with “Network is unreachable”.\\n  - HTTP tests to web99.local and web0.local from these hosts return effectively zero/empty timing, consistent with inability to initiate connections due to lack of IP configuration.\\n\\nImpact: Affected hosts have no end-to-end access to DNS or web services. New clients or clients whose leases expire will experience the same.\\n\\n2) DHCP server not operating\\n- dhcp_server service state:\\n  - systemctl: isc-dhcp-server is inactive (dead).\\n  - No DHCP listener bound: ss -lunp shows no UDP/67.\\n- dhcp_server networking is otherwise sound:\\n  - IP: 10.200.0.8/24 on eth0, default via 10.200.0.1.\\n  - Reachable by infrastructure: pings to 10.200.0.8 from router_dist_1_1, router_dist_2_1, and server_access_router all succeed with low latency.\\n\\nImpact: With the central DHCP service down, DHCP relayed requests from distribution routers cannot be served, leading to hosts not receiving IP addresses.\\n\\nNormal/healthy findings (for context)\\n- Server access segment and routing\\n  - server_access_router br0 has 10.200.0.1/24 and shows OSPF-learned routes to all user subnets (10.1.x.0/24, 10.2.x.0/24).\\n  - Pings from server_access_router to dns_server and dhcp_server succeed.\\n- DNS server availability\\n  - dns_server is listening on TCP 10.200.0.2:53 and 127.0.0.1:53 (netstat).\\n  - DNS host is reachable from distribution and server access layers (ICMP OK).\\n- General path/OSPF health\\n  - OSPF routes are present on server_access_router toward core via eth7 (172.16.0.15/31), indicating OSPF adjacencies and route distribution are functioning.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Faulty device: dhcp_server.\\n- Affected edge: all access VLANs/subnets relying on DHCP relay to 10.200.0.8.\\n- Non-faulty components verified: server_access_router bridging and routing, distribution routers’ reachability to server farm, DNS server process and reachability, backend web server reachability (from infrastructure vantage).\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- The central DHCP service (isc-dhcp-server) on dhcp_server is not running (inactive/dead) and not listening on UDP/67, preventing IP address assignment to hosts via the configured DHCP relay path.\\n\\nEvidence highlights\\n- Host interfaces have no IPv4 configuration and no routes (ip addr/route), causing immediate “Network is unreachable” on pings.\\n- dhcp_server systemctl: inactive (dead); no socket bound for DHCP; yet it is reachable at IP level.\\n- Infrastructure devices can ping DHCP and DNS, and OSPF routes are present, indicating the control-plane and path to the server farm are intact.\\n\\nCurrent network health status\\n- Core/distribution/server-farm: Healthy.\\n- DNS: Healthy and reachable within server-farm/infrastructure.\\n- Load balancer/backend web servers: Reachable from server-farm side; end-user validation not possible due to DHCP outage.\\n- Access/End-user: Impaired due to DHCP service outage; hosts cannot obtain IPs, thus no end-to-end service access from user subnets., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='d55b5a92-df51-44c3-90f8-f96c8aef2eb1'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
